  "content": "When Powerhouse generates code for a document model, it creates React hooks for editor integration. For a `TodoList` model, the generated hook is `useSelectedTodoListDocument`.\n\nUsage pattern:\n```tsx\nconst [selectedTodoList, dispatch] = useSelectedTodoListDocument();\n```\n\nThis provides:\n1. **Document state** (`selectedTodoList`) - The current document including `state.global`, `name`, `operations`, etc.\n2. **Dispatch function** - Send actions to the reducer to modify the document\n\nThe dispatch function works with generated action creators:\n```tsx\nimport { addTodoItem, updateTodoItem, deleteTodoItem } from \"...\";\n\ndispatch(addTodoItem({ text: \"Buy groceries\" }));\ndispatch(updateTodoItem({ id: itemId, checked: true }));\ndispatch(deleteTodoItem({ id: itemId }));\n```\n\nThis follows React's `useReducer` pattern. Any component can use the same hook - you don't need to be in the parent component to dispatch updates. The hook automatically connects to the currently selected document.",
